    date: "2020-09-01",
    author: "Wilson",
    excerpt: "Human activities affect animal behavior through four mechanisms: altering population densities, top-down effects (risk perception), bottom-up effects (resource availability), and physical environment changes. These behavioral shifts can cascade through ecosystems via changes in foraging, movement, communication, and other behaviors, yet the ultimate ecological consequences remain largely uninvestigated.",
