    author: "Stier",
    excerpt: "Pacific herring populations in Haida Gwaii exhibit spatially asynchronous dynamics that buffer regional variability—a portfolio effect. However, commercial harvest and climate have eroded this portfolio over time, with local harvest rates as high as 65% even when archipelago-wide rates appeared sustainable at 15%.",
