    date: "2019-10-08",
    author: "DiFiore",
    excerpt: "Grazing halos—barren areas of sand surrounding coral patch reefs—vary in width from 1-70 meters across Caribbean reef landscapes. A doubling in predator density led to a 29% decrease in grazing intensity, but herbivore density and reef area, not predators, best predicted halo width and the distance herbivores foraged from the reef.",
