    excerpt: "When participation costs in stakeholder meetings are high, only those with extreme positions attend, leading to policy decisions that don't represent the majority. Combined with ecological regime shifts that create stakeholders adapted to the new state, this generates additional inertia preventing return to desired ecosystem states.",
