    date: "2017-06-08",
    author: "Geange",
    excerpt: "The sequence of species colonization (priority effects) had a stronger influence on fish survival than the number of competing individuals (colonizer abundance). Lemon damselfish arriving 3 hours after Ambon damselfish experienced 76% higher mortality, were less aggressive, and avoided competitive interactions more frequently—regardless of how many late-arrivers there were.",
